Pre-Game Insights: Maarten Paes is set to undergo further physical examination due to a minor right ankle injury.
Paes is expected to arrive in Bahrain on October 9th at 14:40 local time.
The team manager, Sumardji, indicates that Paes' condition is improving.
If Paes cannot play, the team will rely on goalkeepers Ernando Ari and Nadeo Argawinata.
The match against Bahrain is crucial for Indonesia's World Cup qualifying campaign.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is significant for Indonesia's journey in qualifying for the 2026 World Cup.
